betterquesting:10.desc:8: This pack is focused on reaching the end game of multiple mods to eventually be able to create the null pointer exception, a mystical crafting ingredient that can create infinite matter. You will have to either learn all the mods or find others to help you progress through all the different mods until you can finally reach the end game.

To get started with Mekanism, you will need a Tinker's Smeltery. You will want to pour 4 redstone dust's worth of molten redstone on an iron ingot to create an enriched alloy, which you will need two of to create the metallurgic infuser.

To gain access to better alloys, you will need to craft a metallurgic infuser. It takes the two infused alloys created in the last quest to make it, as well as a power source. The Mekanism heat generator is a pretty good choice, but not required.
Find some Thaumcraft crystals naturally spawning in caves

Ready to move off of relying on coal to get things smelted? The Energized smelter is a great solution to that problem. It is also the first step towards Mekanism's ore processing line that can go up to 5x the input ores (I think).
Parallelization is a wonderful way to increase the speed that you can process items. This is the first upgrade to the energized smelter, giving it the ability to process 3 items at a time.
Combine 3 vis crystals, a bowl, restone and some flint in a crafting table to create Salis Mundus. (note, you may need to sleep between this quest and the last one)
Your guide to everything thaumic. The questline will provide some general guidance to important things, however, you should mostly follow the thaumonomicon from here on out

Before you get started on Thaumcraft, there are some basics you may want to know.
- §6Observations §rare a resource acquired generally through scanning things with your §bThaumometer§r
- §6Theories§r are a resource acquired through the §bResearch table§r. it's a bit confusing how the table works, play around with it for a bit. you can scan an entire chests worth of items by scanning the chest.
- §6Vis§r is magic in the world around you. Chunks have an amount of vis in them that refills over time
- §6Essentia§r is a liquid form of magic stored in §bWarded Jars§r. you get it by breaking down items into their component aspects
- §6Aspects§r are different elements that essentia is broken up into. most aspects are made up of two component aspects.
- some things in the thaumonomicon are hidden until you do something to reveal it. keep this in mind!
Creating the enrichment chamber is the first step to making more ore per ore. Feeding the ore blocks into this machine, then into a furnace, will double your ores.

For the second tier ore processing setup, you will need both a purification chamber and a crusher.

1. Ore + Oxygen -> Purification chamber -> 2 or 3 Clumps
2. Clumps -> Crusher -> Dirty Dusts -> Enrichment chamber -> Dusts -> Smelted into ingots

Oxygen can be created by electrolyzing water.
Sprinkle some Salis Mundus on a cauldron
brass is certainly made of iron

Now in to quadrupling your yeilds. You will need a chemical injection chamber, a chemical infuser, and a thermal evaporation plant.

1. Ore + Hydrogen Chloride -> Chemical Injection Chamber -> 4 Shards
2. Shards + Oxygen -> Purification Chamber -> 4 Clumps
3. Clumps -> Crusher -> Dirty Dusts -> Enrichment Chamber -> Dusts
4. Dusts -> Smelter -> Ingots

Now on to quintupling your ores! You will need to add a Chemical Dissolution Chamber, Chemical Washer, Rotary Condesentrator, Chemical Crystalizer, and Chemical Oxidizer to your ore processing line.

1. Ore + Sulfuric Acid -> Chemical Dissolution CHamber -> Ore Slurry
2. Ore Slurry + Water -> Chemical Washer -> Clean Ore Slurry -> Chemical Crystalizer -> Crystals
3. Crystals into your tier 3 processing line to finish the process.

If you've played 1.12.2 modded before, you probably know the drill. Get yourself those tables and start building up some tools.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Ore Processing and Metal Tool Parts
betterquesting:10.desc:8: This will be enough material to make a 2x2 smeltery that is one block tall, a decent start to a large smeltery. You can melt down stone and cobblestone into more seared stone, which can be turned into bricks via crafting. This will get you started both on Mekanism, as well as much stronger tools.
Have you ever wanted to chop down an entire tree in one go? Or mine multiple blocks at a time? Upgrading your tool workstation is the way to go.
